<F P=101> Media Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Factions To Fight for Air Time, ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MK0501114094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 5 Jan 94 
p 2 </F>

<F P=103> MK0501114094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report in "In Brief" column] </F>
  [Text] Moscow -- According to Aleksey Vorobyev, press 
secretary of the Democratic Party of Russia, on 6 January 
representatives of State Duma factions formed by deputies of the 
Russian Agrarian Party, the Democratic Party of Russia, and the 
Liberal Democratic Party of Russia intend to meet to discuss 
prospects for resuming the "Parliamentary Hour" TV program and 
according ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA the status of a parliament 
publication. The meeting will take place in Agrarian Party 
headquarters. The deputies plan to ask the remaining five 
factions in the State Duma to support their initiative. 

</TEXT>

