<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military &amp; Space Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Military Chiefs View `New-Generation' Fighter Prototype </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0401130394 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 0655 GMT 2 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PM0401130394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report over video of test flight of new fighter aircraft; </F>
from the "Polygon" program] 
  [Text] [Unidentified correspondent over video of fighter 
aircraft on tarmac and taking off] No awesome name has yet been 
thought up for this aircraft. Its specifications remain secret 
for the time being, but even the first test flight has made it 
clear that what we see here is the super-fighter of the 21st 
century. In terms of flight specifications this fighter has no 
parallel in aviation history. Russian scientists and military 
people believe that this super-fighter will largely determine 
the development of world aircraft building. 
  It is amazing that this machine has appeared now, during a 
period of protracted economic crisis, Deputy Defense Minister 
Andrey Kokoshin and Russian Air Force Commander in Chief Petr 
Deynekin stressed in our interview. 
  [Kokoshin] The first flight has been very successful. I 
consider this an important milestone in the emergence of 
essentially a new-generation aircraft. 
  [Deynekin] I believe that we can confidently and objectively 
claim today that Russia always had, has, and will continue to 
have wings. 

</TEXT>

