<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military &amp; Space Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   General Staff To Carry Out Plans for Downsizing </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MK0401110094 Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS in Russian 4 Jan 
94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> MK0401110094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report under the "Hold the Front Page!" </F>
rubric: "Military Ruse"] 
  [Text] The Russian Defense Ministry's General Staff has 
decided to carry out plans for its own reduction in its own 
manner. 
  It has become known to MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS from reliable 
sources that not a single officer will be discharged from the 
General Staff. There will be a reduction nevertheless. Several 
subunits will be detached from General Staff directorates and 
transformed into several sectors [napravleniya]. All the 
officers will remain in their positions and will not lose even a 
kopeck of their salaries. Defense Ministry chiefs will be able 
to report a 30-percent personnel cut. 
  This is not the first time the military has resorted to such 
a ruse. At one time, the Central Command Post was withdrawn 
from the Main Operations Directorate of the General Staff. 
Those at the top were told about a 50-percent cut. Several 
months after, part of the subunits were taken back. The same 
will happen now too. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

