<H3> <TI>   Baykonur To Launch Soyuz Rocket Complex 8 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0401221494 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1930 GMT 
4 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0401221494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to a report by the press center of the 
Russian military space forces, on 8 January a Soyuz TM-18 rocket 
complex will be launched from the Baykonur cosmodrome. The crew 
consists of the commander, Colonel Viktor Afanasyev, the 
on-board engineer, Yuriy Usachev, and Doctor (Valeriy Polyakov). 
The program of the flight has been arranged in such a way that 
Viktor Afanasyev and Yuriy Usachev will spend 179 days in orbit, 
and Doctor (Valeriy Polyakov) is to spend 429 days in orbit -- 
no one has spent that long of time in space before. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

