<H3> <TI>   Dniester Leaders Fail To Contact Russia's Grachev </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0501075594 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 2021 GMT 3 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0501075594 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tiraspol BASAPRESS, 3/1/1994 -- From our special 
correspondent: Grigore Maracuta, speaker of the Dniester 
Republic's Supreme Soviet, and Viktor Sinyov [name as received], 
deputy premier of the Dniester Republic, have visited Moscow. 
They attempted to have an audience with Russian Minister of 
Defense Pavel Grachev. Reliable sources state that Tiraspol 
representatives intended to suggest Grachev to annul his visit 
to Moldova and Romania and sign some military agreements. 
Maracuta and Sinyov also intended to obtain the transfer of the 
14th Army commander [General Aleksandr Lebed] to another 
military district. However, the audience was not granted. 

</TEXT>

