<H3> <TI>   Talks on Pullout of 14th Army To Take Place in Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0501075494 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 2021 GMT 3 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0501075494 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau BASAPRESS, 3/01/1994 -- The eighth round 
of Moldovan-Russian negotiations on the statute, condition, and 
terms of the 14th Army's withdrawal will take place at the end 
of January in Chisinau, states the Press Secretariat of the 
Moldovan Ministry of Defense. According to sources at this 
Ministry, the previous round was suspended because Moldovan 
representatives insisted, among others, on compensating the 14th 
Army presence in Moldova. Moldovan representatives also 
insisted on 1 July as the final day of the Russian troops' 
withdrawal. Previously, the Press Secretariat of the Ministry 
of Defense made a protest declaration denying Stepan Kitsak's 
affirmations. Stepan Kitsak declared that the Moldovan Ministry 
of Defense took the property and equipment of the Battalion 2 
Cable And Radio of the 14th Army. 

</TEXT>

