<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tiraspol Withdraws Accreditation of Russian Reporter </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0501075294 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 2021 GMT 3 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0501075294 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tiraspol BASAPRESS, 3/01/1994 -- The state 
committee for radio and TV of the self-proclaimed Dniester 
Republic has decided to deny the accreditation of Lev Rozenberg, 
reporter of the Russian EXPRESS KHRONIKA news agency at the 
Tiraspol Supreme Soviet. The reason is an article published in 
EXPRESS KHRONIKA No. 45 regarding some actions of the Tiraspol 
authorities last October, including the voyage of commandos to 
Moscow to defend the White House. Although many Moscow 
publications proved that Tiraspol was involved in the bloodshed, 
it is the first time when Tiraspol authorities deny the 
accreditation of a Russian journalist. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

