<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposition Forces `Mass' on Afghan-Tajik Border </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0401220594 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1930 GMT 
4 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0401220594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Throughout the holidays the operational situation on 
the Tajik-Afghan border remained relatively calm. According to 
a report by the press center of the command of the Russian 
border troops in Tajikistan, no armed provocations were 
registered on any of the sectors. Incidentally, it notes that 
the Tajik opposition armed formations continue to mass on the 
Afghan side. In connection with this, the outposts of the 
Moskovskiy and Pyandzh detachments of the Russian border troops 
and also subunits of Tajikistan's National Security Committee 
are on enhanced combat readiness. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

