<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fresh Clashes Reported on Afghan Border 4 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501102894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0755 
GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0501102894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Gridneva] </F>
  [Text] Dushanbe, 5 Jan -- The ITAR-TASS correspondent has 
learned from sources at the command headquarters of the Russian 
frontier troops in Tajikistan that yesterday afternoon a well 
armed grouping of Tajik fighters tried to invade the territory 
of Tajikistan from Afghanistan in the sector of the outpost of 
the Pyandzh frontier detachment (in the south of the republic). 
As a result of the armed clash, which lasted approximately five 
hours, two of the trespassers were killed and the remainder 
returned to the adjacent bank of the river. Yesterday two armed 
groups also tried to break through in several sections of the 
Pyandzh frontier detachment from the territory of Afghanistan. 
They were, however, halted by the fire of the Russian frontier 
guards. There are no casualties among the Russian servicemen. 
  At the present time, it was stressed at the command 
headquarters, the situation in the sector of the Pyandzh 
frontier detachment is being kept under control by the joint 
actions of the Russian frontier guards and the sub-units of 
Tajikistan's National Security Committee. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

