<F P=101> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pakistan Reportedly Ready To Help in Tajik-Afghan Conflict </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0401151994 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 4 Jan 94 First 
Edition p 4 </F>

<F P=103> PM0401151994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Vladimir Skosyrev report under the "From Our Correspondents </F>
and News Agencies" rubric: "Pakistan Will Help Settle Conflict 
on Afghan-Tajik Border"] 
  [Text] Delhi -- Pakistan is ready to help settle the 
conflict on the border between Afghanistan and Tajikistan. 
  Head of the Pakistani Government Benazir Bhutto explained at 
a press conference on her visit to China that during a recent 
meeting with Afghan President B. Rabbani she had supported his 
policy to improve relations with Tajikistan and other CIS 
states. At the same time the prime minister let it be 
understood that Pakistan does not wish to interfere in the 
disputes between the various armed groupings in Afghanistan, on 
which the situation on the border with Tajikistan depends. 

</TEXT>

