<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Replacement of Soviet Rubles With Russian Rubles Set for 5 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501103194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0833 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0501103194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Gridneva] </F>
  [Text] Dushanbe January 5 TASS -- Under arrangements 
reached by the Governments of Russia and Tajikistan, the 
introduction of Russian money to replace Soviet begins in 
Tajikistan as of this Wednesday [5 January]. Chairman of the 
National Bank Kayum Kavmiddinov announced this on local tv late 
on Tuesday evening. 
  All banknotes with the denomination of five and ten thousand 
roubles will be withdrown from circulatuion as of January 5. 
One thousand, 500 and 100 rouble banknotes will remain valid 
till January 8. Old banknotes held by the population can be put 
on special accounts in savings banks, Kavmiddinov said. When 
all the old banknotes are withdrown, these sums can be taken 
from the accounts. Sums in excess of 200 thousand roubles will 
be put on accounts upon the declaration of incomes. The January 
wages, salaries, pensions and other alowances will be paid in 
new Russian banknotes in the amount not surpassing 32 thousands 
which is equal to four minimum wages. 
  The chairman of the national bank announced the ban on 
taking 
Russian money out of Tajikistan and a temporary stoppage of the 
registration of various commercial enterprises. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

