<F P=100> Uzbekistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Karimov Terms Visit to India `Successful' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0401194594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1818 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0401194594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Sergey Bulantsev] </F>
  [Text] New Delhi January 4 TASS -- "Our visit to India has 
been successful. We have fulfilled all our plans. The visit 
has been rather fruitful. India and Uzbekistan have big 
possibilities for developing cooperation," Uzbekistan's 
President Islam Karimov said. 
  The announcement was made in an interview with ITAR-TASS on 
Tuesday on the second day of Karimov's official visit to India. 
"We have reached understanding with India in the sphere of 
economy and culture, as well as diplomacy and in determining our 
common positions in order to ensure stability in Central Asia 
and the entire region," Karimov stressed. 
  "We are connected with India, this great Asian power with a 
great potential, by both similar mentality and common historic 
roots. Now new possibilities for cooperation are opening up 
before us," he said. 
  On Tuesday, Karimov held talks with Indian Foreign Minister 
Dinesh Singh and Finance Minister Manmohan Singh. He also met 
with representatives of Indian business circles and attended a 
ceremony at the Jawaharlal Nehru University where he was awarded 
an honorary degree of doctor of law. 

</TEXT>

