<F P=100> Uzbekistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Adopts Rules for Distributing Hard Currency Earnings </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0401133794 Tashkent UZBEKISTAN APN in Russian 1101 GMT 4 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0401133794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tashkent UZBEKISTAN APN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Cabinet of Ministers of Uzbekistan has adopted a 
resolution regulating the distribution of hard currency earnings 
of enterprises. According to the resolution, enterprises, 
organizations, and associations of all forms of ownership are 
obliged to pay a 15 percent tax on foreign currency earnings to 
the hard currency fund, and another 15 percent must be sold to 
the republic's Central Bank. On the conclusion of barter 
export-import operations, the amount of earnings will be 
calculated from the value of the contract. Work on special 
measures to monitor the movement of money in foreign currency, 
in order to exclude the possibility of the unauthorized holding 
of money in foreign banks, is also envisaged. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

