<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Turkish Officer Credited With Army Success </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0401152694 Istanbul YENI GUNAYDIN in Turkish 1 Jan 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> NC0401152694 </F>
<F P=104>  Istanbul YENI GUNAYDIN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Ridvan Sapmaz] </F>
  [Text] Baku -- The gradual transition to a regular army is 
the reason for the recent successes scored by the Azerbaijanis 
against the Armenians. The transformation of the Presidential 
Guard, which is directly attached to President Geydar Aliyev, 
into a "regular army" has brought the victory nearer. The 
guardsmen are being trained at a location some 50-km from Baku 
to adapt to any natural environment. The Azerbaijani commanders 
in their turn have been trained by the officers of the Turkish 
Armed Forces. 
<H5>  The Discipline of the Turkish Army </H5>
  The [Azerbaijani] commanders are saying: "We were trained by 
Turkish officers. Had we received this training beforehand, the 
Armenians would not have been able to occupy our lands." 
Indicating that their military discipline is fashioned after 
the discipline in the Turkish Army, the commanders are saying: 
"The Armenians will now see how we fight. The previous defeats 
were not our fault. The volunteer units were the cause for our 
reverses. Any person wanting to fight must fight under the 
command of the national army." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

