<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Draft Constitution `Almost Completed' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0401150194 Moscow PRAVDA in Russian 4 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM0401150194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow PRAVDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report from the PRAVDA, ITAR-TASS column: "With No Haste </F>
or Fuss"] 
  [Text] A draft new Azerbaijan Constitution will be 
submitted for parliamentary debate this spring. 
  The working group preparing the draft has almost completed 
work on the text. Nonetheless, it still has to be "polished." 
The experience of the independent states proclaimed following 
the collapse of the Union has shown that the adoption of a 
constitution that is new in content is a protracted and 
labor-intensive process. It would be inappropriate to rush such 
an important job. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

