<F P=102>  LD0501120494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0653 
GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0501120494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valentina Ivanova] </F>
  [Text] Cheboksary, 5 Jan -- Boris Yeltsin greeted Nikolay 
Fedorov on his election as Chuvashia's first president. 
  "I am confident that you will proceed further with economic 
reforms for the sake of making the life of the Chuvash people 
dignified and that you will facilitate the strengthening of 
Russia's constitutional foundations. I look forward to carrying 
out constructive work together," emphasized the Russian 
Federation president in his telegram. 
  Today SOVETSKAYA CHUVASHIA published the presidential 
greetings as the first message on a whole page of similar 
greetings which continue to arrive for the 35 year old former 
Russian Justice Minister Nikolay Fedorov, who was elected to 
Chuvashia's highest state post on New Year's eve. 

