<H3> <TI>   Chechnya Plans `Neighborhood Watch' Teams To Maintain Order </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0401150994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1137 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0401150994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Chechen leaders are planning to organize 
neighborhood watch teams and mobile militia groups to maintain 
order around the clock. According to Interfax sources, such 
posts will be set up along Groznyy's perimeter and on the 
approaches to the city. 
  This question was discussed during talks between President 
Dzhokhar Dudayev and representatives of law-enforcement bodies. 
The talks also resulted in the decision to establish 
headquarters for coordinating the newly set-up detachments. The 
headquarters' work will be controlled by the president, who is 
also chairman of the Chechen Security Council. 

</TEXT>

