<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Economic Freedom Party has expressed readiness 
to mediate in organizing talks between Russia and Chechnya. 
According to Interfax sources, the party's message to Chechen 
President Dzhokhar Dudayev points to the necessity "to resume 
the dialogue and restore the ruptured links." 
  Without mutual understanding with Chechnya, there will be 
neither peace nor tranquility in the south of Russia. Neither 
can the future of the Chechen people be based on constant 
confrontation with Russia or on isolation from the world 
community, says the message. 

