<H3> <TI>   Israel To Supply Arms, Border Protection Equipment </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0401132194 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 4 Jan 94 First 
Edition p 4 </F>

<F P=103> PM0401132194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Leonid Levitskiy: "Israel Selling Arms to </F>
Estonia and Supplying Equipment for Its Borders"] 
  [Text] Tallinn -- The Estonian Government is taking 
measures to strengthen security along the republic's borders. 
  Electronic devices have already replaced the traditional 
barbed wire in many countries. Estonia also intends to protect 
itself in this way. Italy, Sweden, France, and Israel have 
offered it their electronic systems. The government discussed 
these offers together with the conclusions of experts. As Prime 
Minister Mart Laar announced at a press conference, the only 
scheme for guarding the land border which deserved any attention 
was the one Israel had put forward. It is with Israel that 
negotiations will be held. 
  According to the prime minister, electronic equipment will 
be 
set up along the full length of the border for a certain time. 
But the border with Latvia will in the future become 
unprotected. All equipment from it will be transferred to the 
Estonian-Russian border. 
  Israel has also concluded a contract to supply Estonia with 
arms worth $50 million on credit. There are enough of them for 
the whole Estonian Army. 

</TEXT>

