<F P=102>  WS0401193394 Tallinn ETA NEWS RELEASE in English 1758 GMT 4 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS0401193394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA NEWS RELEASE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tallinn, January 4 -- "Russian Liberal Democratic 
Party has its daughter organization in Estonia," Pyotr Rozhok 
who was active as Vladimir Zhirinovskiy's Estonian 
representative already before general elections in Russia, told 
ETA. 
  Rozhok who said he was Zhirinovskiy's advisor, but not head 
of the Estonian organization, refused to disclose the size of 
the party's Estonian branch. 
  "Also members of other parties can join our party, even if 
they are communists," Rozhok said while adding that membership 
fee was 100 rubles and admission fee ten rubles. 
  Rozhok said one of the party's tasks in Estonia was to 
provide Zhirinovskiy with materials on Baltics while adding that 
during election campaign Zhirinovskiy had made abundant use of 
the information. 
  "When the right time comes, we will tell more about 
ourselves 
and our activities," he said. 

