<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Danish Delegation Meets Ulmanis, Visits Skrunda </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0401195394 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1800 GMT 4 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0401195394 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Latvian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A delegation of the Danish Ministry of Defense today 
visited the the Russian army unit at Skrunda. Speaking at a 
press briefing at the Ministry of Defense, Danish Defense 
Minister Hans Haekkerup acknowledged that Russia undoubtedly has 
military-strategic interests in Latvia. However, no country has 
the right to maintain its troops in another state against its 
will. 
  At Skrunda the Danish delegation met the leading personnel 
of 
the radar station and listened to a lecture on the activities 
and functions of this station. The guests were not denied a 
chance to examine the station's technical equipment. After that 
the delegation of the Danish Ministry of Defense visited the 
Kuldiga Home Guard battalion. 
  President Guntis Ulmanis also met the Danish minister of 
defense today. Ulmanis noted that this is the first foreign 
delegation to make close acquaintance with the Skrunda radar 
station. The president also appreciatively assessed the 
cooperation agreement signed between the defense forces of 
Latvia and Denmark, and noted that the three main issues in 
talks with Russia directly concern the Skrunda radar station. 
  The Danish defense minister offered the assistance of his 
specialists in ascertaining the harmful effects of the station. 
He was also appreciative of the creation of a unified peace 
battalion for the Baltic countries. Haekkerup and Ulmanis also 
discussed the idea of the common security system for Europe, and 
exchanged views on the NATO summit to be held in January, which 
will also decide on the inclusion of east European countries in 
these structures. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

