<F P=102>  WS0401163694 Tallinn BNS in English 1001 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0401163694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vilnius, Jan 04, BNS -- The principal aim of the 
Russian company Lucoil, the chief supplier of oil to Lithuania, 
is "to increase prices and to rob people" without even having to 
compete, said Vytautas Landsbergis, leader of the Lithuanian 
parliament's rightist opposition. 
  The continuing story of Lithuanian oil terminal construction 
proves that Lithuania's energy system is still dependent on 
other countries, he said. 
  Landsbergis said energy prices in Estonia are going down 
because it imports fuel from the West, while Lithuania makes up 
the "Lucoil myth" to justify the absence of alternative fuel 
sources. 

</TEXT>

