<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Council for Coordination of Foreign Policy Meets </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0401164094 Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network in Lithuanian 
1400 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0401164094 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Lithuanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Nerijus Maliukevicius, the Lithuanian President's 
spokesman for the press reported that the first sitting of the 
Council for Coordination of Foreign Policy was held today at the 
president's office. The council is headed by Lithuanian 
President Algirdas Brazauskas. 
  Prime Minister Adolfas Slezevicius, Lithuanian Seimas 
Chairman Ceslovas Jursenas, Foreign Minister Povilas Gylys, 
National Defense Minister Linas Linkevicius, and Justas 
Paleckis, the president's adviser on foreign policy, took part 
in today's sitting. 
  The Council for Coordination of Foreign Policy was set up on 
9 December of last year by decree of the president. The 
objective of the council is to coordinate actions in foreign 
policy among the government institutions and to aim for an 
effective implementation of these actions, as well as to discuss 
proposals concerning the execution of foreign policy. 
  Two items on today's agenda were discussed: The first item 
was Lithuania's cooperation with the European Union and the 
expansion of NATO, and the second issue was on future visits to 
foreign countries by Lithuanian top government officials and 
future visits to Lithuania by officials and leaders of foreign 
countries. 
  Brazauskas is to make a statement on today's Lithuanian TV 
Panorama program on one of the issues discussed. 

</TEXT>

