<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Envoy Strives To Dispel Myths on Relations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0501090494 Vilnius ELTA in Lithuanian 1141 GMT 3 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0501090494 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius ELTA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Lithuanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Before the New Year, Professor Jan Widacki, Polish 
ambassador extraordinary and plenipotentiary to Lithuania, 
invited journalists to a press conference in which he tried to 
dispel the myths about the allegedly unfriendly relations 
between the Lithuanians and the Poles. According to the 
ambassador, these myths are spread by some politicians and 
reporters. 
  One of those myths is the opinion expressed in the 
Lithuanian 
press that Poland either had or has such political and social 
groups that raise territorial claims to Lithuania. 
  The ambassador assured that this is not the case, and that 
the Polish Government recognizes Lithuania's territorial status 
quo. 
  Jan Widacki also expressed his surprise with the statements 
that some "third party" is behind the issue of the registration 
of the Home Army veterans' club in Lithuania. He ruled out the 
proposal examined in the Lithuanian press that this club be 
registered at some Lithuanian veterans' organization or function 
within the framework of the Poles' Union. 
  To reduce such misunderstandings, the ambassador proposed 
that journalists of both countries meet for seminars at least 
twice a year. 
  In Jan Widacki's opinion, the journalists' duty is to dispel 
myths which emerged in relations between the Lithuanian and 
Polish nations rather than on the interstate level. 

</TEXT>

