<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   GMM Moscow Office Denies Funding Zhirinovskiy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MK0501105094 Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS in Russian 5 Jan 
94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> MK0501105094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report under the "Hold the Front Page!" </F>
rubric: "GMM at the Peak of Problems" ] 
  [Text] "The GMM [Global Money Management] company has 
nothing to do with bankrolling any Russian parties or blocs, 
even less so Zhirinovskiy," our correspondent was told by 
Aleksandr Liozner, head of the company's Moscow office, 
responding to accusations in a number of mass media. "All this 
can be easily checked against bank documents. As for Aleksey 
Zuyev, elected deputy of the State Duma from the Liberal 
Democratic Party of Russia, he never worked for GMM and no work 
agreements were concluded with him. The position of "adviser to 
the president," he indicated, has never existed in the 
company...." 
  According to our information, GMM will take action against 
Mikhail Leontyev and the newspaper SEGODNYA tomorrow. At this 
stage the firm plans to hold a series of consultations with the 
Central Bank, which has suspended GMM operations. Mr. 
Shakhovtsov, head of the Central Bank banking supervision 
section, has said that in the absence of legislation on trust 
companies, the operation of GMM pertains equally to that of a 
trust and of a banking company. 
  In Zhirinovskiy's headquarters, it was said to our request 
for comments on the situation that the Liberal Democratic Party 
of Russia absolutely did not care about GMM's problems, and that 
the party was busy devising plans to destroy Germany, which had 
refused its leader an entry visa. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

