<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Indignation' Expressed Over Russians' Murder in Tajikistan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501152294 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1100 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0501152294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Valeriy Vinogradov ; from the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] We have just received a statement of the Foreign 
Ministry of the Russian Federation, which states: The 
leadership of the Russian Federation has received with profound 
grief and indignation the report of the brutal murders carried 
out in recent days in Tajikistan of Russian-speaking citizens -- 
a deacon of the Orthodox Church, a whole family including five 
children, and a young woman resident of Dushanbe. We are firmly 
relying on the fact that the Tajikistan authorities will take 
the most energetic measures in investigating what has happened 
and in speedily identifying and suitably punishing the 
murderers. We also expect that the Government of Tajikistan 
will do everything necessary to ensure the security and the 
protection of the rights and dignity of the Russian-speaking 
citizens of the republic. 

</TEXT>

