<H3> <TI>   Russian Forces To Be Out of Germany by 31 Aug </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0401214194 Moscow Radio Moscow in Russian to Tajikistan 
1700 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0401214194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Moscow </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Radio Slavyanka" program of the Russian Defense </F>
Ministry] 
  [Text] Russian troops are to be finally withdrawn from 
Germany by 31 August 1994, said Colonel General Matvey Burlakov, 
commander in chief of the Western Group of Forces, at a meeting 
in Wuensdorf with Manfred Stolpe, president of Brandenburg land. 
During the meeting both sides agreed on joint efforts for the 
withdrawal of Russian troops from Brandenburg, including from 
Wuensdorf, where the headquarters of the Western Group of Forces 
is situated. 

