<H3> <TI>   First Exercise With Kuwaiti Navy Ends in Gulf </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0401151694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1258 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0401151694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Aleksandr Yelistratov] </F>
  [Text] Cairo January 4 TASS -- The first joint exercise of 
Kuwaiti and Russian naval forces ended in the Persian Gulf on 
Tuesday. The exercise lasting 12 days involved several Kuwaiti 
warships as well as a large anti-submarine ship, the Admiral 
Vinogradov, a large landing ship, the Nikolay Vilkov, and an 
auxiliary vessel of the Russian Navy. 
  The exercise was carried out in conformity with a treaty on 
joint defence between the two countries which was concluded late 
last November. 
  According to military observers, it was conducted at a high 
professional level. All tasks set forth before the crews were 
successfully fulfilled. 
  Referring to a statement by the spokesman of the Kuwaiti 
Defence Ministry, the Sawt al-Arab radio station reported on 
Tuesday that preparations are now in progress to conduct another 
Kuwaiti-Russian exercise which will involve all services -- the 
navies, air forces and land troops. 

</TEXT>

