<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shushkevich Signs CIS Security Agreement With `Reservations' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501174794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1714 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0501174794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By BELINFORM correspondent Larisa Lazar for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Minsk January 5 TASS -- Belarusian Parliament head 
Stanislav Shushkevich has sent a letter to the CIS executive 
secretariat to confirm that Belarus has signed the CIS 
collective security agreement, the parliamentary press service 
announced today. 
  The press-service said the problem had to be addressed anew 
because the procedure of the preliminary signing of the 
agreement was interpreted incorrectly by some officials. 
  The parliament empowered its head, Stanislav Shushkevich "to 
sign the agreement on collective security after making a 
statement on certain reservations," it said. 
  These reservations "rule out in particular the use of 
Belarusian Armed Forces on the territory of other countries, and 
the stationing and use of Armed Forces of other states on the 
Belarusian territory without the express permission of the 
Belarusian Parliament," the press-service said. 

</TEXT>

