<H3> <TI>   Deputy Premier Views Recent Murders of Russians </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501234694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1912 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0501234694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The recent murders of Russians in Tajikistan are of 
a purely criminal character as they are neither religiously, nor 
politically nor ethnically colored, Tajik Vice Prime Minister 
Makhamadsayed Ubaidullayev told a briefing in Dushanbe today. 
  Ubaidullayev said four suspects of a murder of nine people 
in 
the village of Novobad near Dushanbe late at night on December 
30 were arrested yesterday. He added that the suspects did not 
conceal that they had committed the crime with the aim of 
robbery. 
  Ubaidullayev also said that the motive for the murder of 
Father Sergy, a priest of the Russian Orthodox Church in 
Dushanbe on the same night, still remained unclear. The 
investigating bodies were working on a number of likely 
versions, the high official said. 
  The Tajik Interior Ministry announced a considerable 
financial reward for information helping to solve the case. 
  On behalf of the republican government, Ubaidullayev 
expressed condolences to the family and friends of the murdered. 

</TEXT>

