<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rebirth Party Leader Stresses Talks With Russia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501210594 (Clandestine) Voice of Free Tajikistan in Tajik 
0600 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0501210594 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of Free Tajikistan </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Tajik </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] His eminence Haji Akbar Turajonzoda, first deputy 
leader of the Islamic Rebirth Party of Tajikistan, has once 
again stated that the Russian troops stationed in Tajikistan 
together with UN forces, under the supervision of Islamic 
countries and the European Community, can play the role of 
peacekeeping and take part in disarming the warring side. 
  Haji Akbar said: We too understand the geopolitical 
interests of Russia and do not want to deprive Russia of them 
[words indistinct]. 
  Haji Akbar once again reiterated that the Islamic Rebirth 
Party of Tajikistan will first hold talks with Russia. Talks 
with Russia will determine the course of our future negotiations 
with the authorities in Tajikistan. 

</TEXT>

