<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Azerbaijani Attacks Reported Escalated </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0501144194 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1400 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0501144194 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1400 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Military operations are escalating on the Karabakh 
front every day. Disregarding huge losses in men and material, 
the Azerbaijani Army Command is launching uninterrupted new 
offensives against the defensive positions of the Karabakh 
forces. 
  The Nagorno-Karabakh Republic's Press and Information 
Department reported that the enemy troops launched a new 
offensive at around 0600 this morning all along the frontline 
from the Iranian border to the Murov mountain range in the north 
of Mardakertskiy Rayon. The Karabakh formations were still 
successfully halting the Azerbaijani attacks at 1100. 
  According to preliminary reports, an enemy tank was hit and 
some 150 soldiers and officers are surrounded in the southeast 
of the front. 
  Casualty figures for the previous day have been determined. 
Karabakh fighters killed 140 Azerbaijani soldiers, destroyed 
four tanks, and an infantry vehicle. Five fighters were killed 
and one tank was hit on our side. 
  We have no news from the Armenian Defense Ministry Press 
Service on the situation in Armenia's border regions. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

