<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Sends Message to PRC's Qian Qichen </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501194994 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1321 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0501194994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kiev -- A UNIAN correspondent was informed at the 
Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Ukraine on 4 January that Foreign 
Minister Anatoliy Zlenko, has sent a personal message to Qian 
Qichen, vice premier of the State Council and minister of 
foreign affairs of the People's Republic of China, in connection 
with the second anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic 
links between Ukraine and China. In particular the letter notes 
that "China became one of the first states in the world to 
recognize Ukraine, establish diplomatic relations with it, and 
open its embassy in Kiev. China's attitude to the development 
of relations with Ukraine is highly valued in our young country. 
The visits to China by Leonid Kravchuk, president of Ukraine, 
and Ivan Plyushch, chairman of the Supreme Council, in this 
short period of time have demonstrated this." 
  It was reported at the Ministry of Foreign Affairs that the 
legal and contractual basis of inter-state relations between 
both states has been elaborated much better than that with many 
other states which had stronger links with Ukraine prior to the 
break-up of the USSR. Twelve documents were signed during the 
visit to China by Leonid Kravchuk in 1992 alone, some of which 
have already been ratified by both parliaments. According to 
information of the Ministry of Foreign Economic Relations of 
Ukraine, according to the results for 1993, China is the leader 
in the East Asian region in volume of exports from Ukraine. The 
People's Republic of China purchases road technology, electrical 
equipment, timber, cement, metal, pipes, fittings, and other 
goods from us. The structure of products imported from China is 
distributed almost evenly between products of light and textile 
industries, products of the conversion of the Chinese 
military-industrial complex, and agricultural produce. 
  A reception on the occasion of the second anniversary of the 
establishment of diplomatic relations between the two states 
took place at the embassy of the People's Republic of China in 
Ukraine on 4 January. Yuriy Rylach, deputy minister of foreign 
affairs of Ukraine, who was present at the reception, expressed 
the hope for further fruitful development of interstate 
relations. Ivan Drach, chairman of the "Ukraine" society; Petro 
Myroshnykov, chairman of the Ukrainian-Chinese friendship 
society; and Valentyn Lipatov, deputy minister of foreign 
affairs of Ukraine, were also present at the reception. Zhang 
Zhen, ambassador of the People's Republic of China in Ukraine, 
thanked the guests from ministries and departments of Ukraine, 
the active members of the Ukrainian-Chinese friendship society, 
and representatives from business circles of the capital and 
from the diplomatic corps for their attention and cooperation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

