<H3> <TI>   Black Sea Naval Engineers Swear Allegiance </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MK0501141094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 5 Jan 94 
p 3 </F>

<F P=103> MK0501141094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report under the "NEGA Reports" rubric: </F>
"Crimea"] 
  [Text] Officers of the Black Sea Fleet naval engineering 
service departments in Nikolayev and Odessa have voluntarily 
taken the oath of allegiance to Ukraine. In a briefing held at 
the Black Sea Fleet press center devoted to these events, it was 
however stated that the transfer of Black Sea Fleet naval 
engineering service departments to the subordination of 
Ukraine's Navy and Defense Ministry had been taking place with 
the aid of submachine gunners. The Black Sea Fleet command 
believes that such actions were sanctioned by Ukraine. 

