<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister on Clashes, `Mercenaries' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0501181294 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1600 
GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0501181294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Azerbaijani Defense Minister Mamedrafi Mamedov has 
stated that the Armenian Army started to attack on all fronts 
but that it was forced to withdraw as a result of the large 
number of soldiers wounded and killed following the Azerbaijan 
national army's resistance. Mamedov was interviewed by Ismail 
Karadavud, TRT correspondent in Baku. 
  [Begin Karadavud recording] In a statement he issued to TRT, 
Mamedov pointed out that the Armenians have not been able to 
advance during the last month, adding that approximately 200 to 
300 Armenian soldiers were being killed in clashes every day. 
Mamedov reported that 19 Armenian tanks and a large number of 
military vehicles have been destroyed since the beginning of the 
new year. Mamedov further reported that approximately 100 Azeri 
soldiers were killed and 50 wounded in clashes between the 
Azerbaijani national army and Armenian units over the last 
month. Pointing out that both the Azeri people and their army 
will defend their territory until the last drop of their blood, 
Mamedov noted that the people of Kelbadzhar have started 
returning after the Armenians evacuated the area. 
  Mamedov stated that a large number of mercenaries from 
various nations are fighting in the Armenian Army, announcing 
that one of those mercenaries was being held by the Azerbaijani 
Army. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

