<H3> <TI>   `Great Losses' Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501140294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1131 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0501140294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baku and Stepanakert are still reporting great 
losses during fierce fighting in the zone of the 
Armenian-Azerbaijani conflict. 
  A well informed source in Azerbaijan's Defense Minister 
asserted in his interview with Interfax that several dozen 
Armenian soldiers were killed on Tuesday [4 January] during the 
hostilities waged near the Murovdag mountain ridge on the border 
of the Kelbadzharskiy and Agderin (Mardakertskiy) regions. Two 
artillery guns of the Karabakh army have been destroyed. 
  According to Baku, the Armenians lost two tanks and an APC 
[armored personnel carrier] on other sections of the front. 
  Meanwhile, sources in Stepanakert assert that the 
Azerbaijani army lost more than 70 soldiers, 4 tanks and one APC 
during the hostilities Tuesday. 
  Stepanakert also asserts that the Karabakh party lost only 
three servicemen. 

</TEXT>

