<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aliyev Accepts Invitation To Visit UK </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0501183994 Baku AZERTAC in English 1530 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0501183994 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku AZERTAC </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baku, January 5 (AZERTAC)--The Azerbaijani President 
Geydar Aliyev has accepted an invitation sent by Great Britain 
Prime-Minister, Mr. John Major for an official visit to this 
European country, according to the press-service of the 
Azerbaijani leader. The trip is likely to take place by the end 
of January. It is supposed that the Azerbaijani Embassy in 
London will be opened at the same time. 
  According to the Foreign Ministry of Azerbaijan, Mr. Geydar 
Aliyev in his turn has invited the head of the British 
Government to pay a visit to the Republic at any convenient time. 
  Officials in Baku stress the great importance of the 
development and intensification of relations with Great Britain, 
which was among the first states that established diplomatic 
relations with independent Azerbaijan. The two countries have 
already signed a protocol on economic cooperation and ratified 
documents on cooperation on Foreign Ministry level, as well as a 
memorandum on unlimited freedom of movement for British citizens 
in Azerbaijan. 
  At present, Great Britain has taken a leading position in 
the 
external economic relations of Azerbaijan coming third after 
Iran and Turkey. A number of leading British companies such as 
British Petroleum, JPT communication, Worldwide, Kaizer 
Engineering have already installed themselves. The first of 
these is going to take part in joint exploration and 
exploitation of off-shore oil fields and according to experts, 
has got excellent opportunities. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

