<H3> <TI>   Gasanov Talks With PRC's Li Peng in Beijing </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501223294 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1334 
GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0501223294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [by ITAr-TASS correspondent Vladimir Fedoruk] </F>
  [Text] Beijing, 5 Jan -- Li Peng, premier of the PRC State 
Council, today expressed satisfaction at the development of 
Chinese-Azerbaijani relations. During the course of a meeting 
with Azerbaijani Foreign Minister Gasan Gasanov, who is here on 
an official visit, the head of the Chinese Government noted the 
"solid and healthy relations" between the two states since the 
establishment of diplomatic relations. 
  The premier stressed that the PRC attaches great 
significance 
to the development of bilateral relations with Azerbaijan. 
China and Azerbaijan are Asian countries, and friendly contacts 
between their peoples go back 2,000 years, to the time of the 
"Great Silk Road," he said. 
  Li Peng welcomed the planned visit to China of the 
Azerbaijani president, noting that an "exchange of visits at 
high level will undoubtedly foster the development of relations" 
between the two countries. 
  According to XINHUA, G. Gasanov, stressed Azerbaijan's 
desire 
to establish close cooperation with China in various spheres. 
He also highly appraised the results of the economic reforms 
now being carried out in China. 

</TEXT>

