<H3> <TI>   Institute To Help Construct Baku Gold Plant </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0501162394 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 5 Jan 94 
First Edition p 3 </F>

<F P=103> PM0501162394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report from roundup of RIA-NOVOSTI and INTERFAX reports] </F>
  [Text] The first plant in Azerbaijan for the production of 
gold ingots with a fineness of 999.9 will be constructed in Baku 
in cooperation with the Moscow "Geotep" institute. 
  The Muscovites have developed the technological part of the 
project for the future enterprise and handed over the blueprints 
to representatives of the client -- the "Azerkyzyl" 
("Azerzoloto") state company. This was announced by "Azerkyzyl" 
Vice President Valis Ismaylov. "Geotep," he noted, has assumed 
the purchase of specialized equipment and its delivery to the 
construction site. 
  Predicted gold reserves in Azerbaijan are assessed at 1,500 
tonnes. At the same time other precious metals, silver in 
particular, will be mined with it. 
  The planned capacity of the first gold extracting plant is 
five tonnes of ingots a year. It will be possible to reach this 
level three to four years after the launch of the enterprise. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

