<H3> <TI>   Reportage on Zviad Gamsakhurdia's Death </TI></H3>
<H4>   TASS Reports `Suicide' </H4>
<F P=102> LD0501145694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1428 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0501145694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Mikhail Shevtsov] </F>
  [Text]Moscow, January 5 TASS -- Ex-President of Georgia 
Zviad Gamsakhurdia committed suicide in one of the districts of 
western Georgia on December 31, 1993. 
  Gamsakhurdia's death was announced by his wife Manana. She 
said the place, where her husband happened to be at that time, 
was surrounded by unidentified men. According to her version, 
"the Georgian authorities are aware of Gamsakhurdia's death, but 
have carefully concealed the fact to this day." 

</TEXT>

