<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage on Zviad Gamsakhurdia's Death </TI></H3>
<H4>   Press Service Makes Statement </H4>
<F P=102> LD0501151694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1448 
GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0501151694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Mikhail Shevtsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 5 January -- Zviad Gamsakhurdia, 
ex-president of Georgia, committed suicide at 0030 on 31 
December 1993 [2130 GMT on 30 December] in a region of western 
Georgia. 
  An ITAR-TASS correspondent learned today from the Chechen 
president's press service that Zviad Gamsakhurdia's wife Manana 
had noted that the place where Zviad Gamsakhurdia spent that 
night had been surrounded by unknown persons. According to her 
version, "the Georgian authorities had information about 
Gamsakhurdia's death but carefully concealed it and are still 
concealing it to this moment." 
  A statement issued in Groznyy today by Zviad Gamsakhurdia's 
press service notes that a few minutes before his death he said 
that "he is committing this act in full awareness as a sign of 
protest against the existing regime in Georgia and of his 
inability, as president, to improve the situation and to restore 
legality and law and order." 

</TEXT>

