<H3> <TI>   Trial Begins for Murder of U.S. Official </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501135594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1131 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0501135594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The trial of Anzor Sharmaidze, 21, charged with the 
murder of Fred Woodruff, an official of the American Embassy in 
Georgia, began in Tbilisi on Wednesday [5 January]. 
  Before the trial the lawyer of the unemployed defendant made 
a statement claiming the murder was a tragic accident. 
  The trial taking place at the Supreme Court is attended by 
the vice-consul of the American embassy. 
  Woodruff was killed last summer on a highway near Tbilisi. 
Investigators arrived at the conclusion an attempt was made to 
stop the diplomat's car for the purpose of robbery. As the car 
driven by the chief of Shevardnadze's security did not stop, 
fire was opened at it. 
  According to many sources, Woodruff was a CIA officer. The 
chief of the organization James Woolsey came to Tbilisi to 
escort the dead body back home. 

</TEXT>

