<F P=106> [By GIA correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Tbilisi January 5 TASS -- In today's interview with 
national television, Georgian Head of State Eduard Shevardnadze 
cited the republic's entering the Commonwealth of Independent 
States as one of the last year's most important events. 
  Analysing the current political and economic situation in 
Georgia, Shevardnadze listed three principal factors which he 
believes should determine joint activities within the CIS 
