<H3> <TI>   Russian Delegation Arrives in Abkhazia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501221594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1831 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0501221594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Zurab Argun] </F>
  [Text] Sukhumi January 5 TASS -- A delegation of the 
Russian Federation led by Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Boris 
Pastukhov arrived in Sukhumi on Wednesday. 
  In an interview with ITAR-TASS Pastukhov said that the 
delegation arrived in Abkhazia to familiarise itself with the 
situation in Abkhazia on the eve of Georgian-Abkhazian talks due 
to begin in Geneva on January 11. 
  A meeting between Pastukhov and Vladislav Ardzinba was held 
in the residence of the Abkhazian parliament chairman. After 
the talks with Abkhazian leaders the Russian delegation met with 
the people of the Abkhazian capital Sukhumi and visited 
districts damaged during military operations. 
  Pastukhov positively assessed efforts made by the Abkhazian 
government to eliminate the after-effects of the war and improve 
the social position of the Abkhazian population. 
  Pastukhov expressed the hope for the speediest solution of 
problems connected with the return of refugees who fled the 
republic during the war. 
  On Thursday, the Russian delegation is leaving for Moscow. 

</TEXT>

