<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Democratic Bloc Condemns Rukh for Nomination of Candidates </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501143994 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 2300 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0501143994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kiev, 4 Jan -- The second working sitting has taken 
place of the the All-Ukrainian Electoral Committee of the 
Democratic Association bloc, which unites parties and 
organizations of national democratic orientation such as Rukh 
[People's Movement of Ukraine], URP [Ukrainian Republican 
Party], DemPU [Democratic Party of Ukraine], KUN [Congress of 
Ukrainian Nationalists], Prosvita [Enlightenment], SOU [Union of 
Officers of Ukraine], and others. Chaired by the URP honorary 
chairman, Levko Lukyanenko, the sitting considered and 
coordinated lists of the bloc's candidates in separate Ukrainian 
regions. Rukh was accused of destructive activity in that some 
local NRU organizations, in particular the one in Kharkov, in 
spite of prior arrangement had composed lists of candidates of 
their own. People's Council Chairman Ivan Zayets brushed aside 
these accusations saying that this situation was the result of 
the sluggishness of other organizations who had not made up 
their mind yet exactly in which districts to nominate their 
candidates. It was decided to organize regional tours by 
leaders of the bloc's parties to settle contentious issues 
locally. The second part of the sitting discussed the name of 
the bloc and its pre-election slogans. 

</TEXT>

