<H3> <TI>   Trade Union Election Platform Advocates `Civilized' Reform </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0501203694 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 2000 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS0501203694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Ukrainian Trade Union Presidium has approved 
the organization's platform for the upcoming legislative 
elections. The trade unions advocate civilized market reform 
carried out under the slogan: Humane life for the man of labor. 
The platform, in particular, stipulates the formation of a 
reliable legislative footing for an efficient social system for 
the people, a radical improvement of working conditions and 
living standards, the introduction of flexible work schedules, a 
shorter work week, and an increase in social payments. 

</TEXT>

