<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Crimean-Tatar Movement Opposes Majlis Boycott of Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501221294 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 1430 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0501221294 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Simferopol, 5 Jan -- The Crimean-Tatar People's 
Majlis has called on its countrymen to boycott the Crimean 
Republic presidential elections since none of the candidates 
promises to meet the Crimean-Tatar people's demands. According 
to a recent statement by a majlis leader, the majlis has 
indisputable influence over an absolute majority of voters among 
the Crimean-Tatars. 
  On the other hand, Vashtiy Abdurayimov, the leader of the 
National Movement of Crimean Tatars, who became head of the 
organization after the death of its founder and leader Yuriy 
Osmanov, stressed that the majlis was in fact betraying the 
national interests of the Crimean Tatars. In Abdurayimov's 
opinion, the Crimean Tatars must by all means vote in the 
Crimean presidential elections in order to elect a president who 
would more or less suit the Crimean-Tatar people. According to 
some sources, Abdurayimov is inclined to support the candidacy 
of Ivan Yermakov, Ukraine's presidential representative in 
Sevastopol, deputy chairman of the Crimean Supreme Council [as 
received]. 
  Majlis leader Mustafa Dzhamilev is known to have recently 
met 
President Kravchuk. Although the results of the talks are not 
known, local observers believe they reached a certain, if not 
full understanding. 

</TEXT>

