<H3> <TI>   Estimates Say Living Standards Below Survival Level </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501144494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1125 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0501144494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By BUSINESS-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, January 5 (TASS) -- The latest prices hike 
has compelled many Ukrainian families to reduce their spendings 
substantially, BUSINESS-TASS has learned today from the 
Ukrainian NORMA-PRESS NEWS SERVICE. Today, according to expert 
estimates, the physiologial survival basket costs 383,996 
karbovanets, which is double the november figure. 
  A more or less normal minimum consumer basket, comprising 
twenty products, now costs 900,738 karbovanets, while the 
average wages are much lower than that. NORMA-PRESS economists 
stress that all the measures taken by the government to raise 
minimal wages, pensions, scholarships, and allowances to poor 
families leave these sections of the population without any hope 
for even purely physiological survival. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

