<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Danish Minister Ends Visit, Pledges Assistance </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501131194 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1000 GMT 5 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0501131194 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Latvian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Your problems are also our problems: With these 
words, Danish Defense Minister Hans Haekkerup today ended his 
lecture at the Latvian National Defense Academy. He also ends 
his visit to Latvia today. 
  In the lecture at the National Defense Academy, the Danish 
defense minister was explaining resolutions that will probably 
be passed at the summit meeting of the NATO member states in 
Brussels on 10 January. At the end of his lecture, Haekkerup 
promised that Denmark would also be granting to Latvia all kinds 
of assistance in the future. 
  Haekkerup also held a news conference this morning about his 
visit to Kurzeme province yesterday. He visited the Russian 
military facility--the Skrunda radar station and the 45th 
Kuldiga battalion of the Latvian Home Guard. Haekkerup stressed 
that the radar station should not be left in Latvia and that the 
dismantling of the radar should be agreed on at Latvian-Russian 
talks. Haekkerup also positively assessed the Latvian Home Guard. 

</TEXT>

