<H3> <TI>   Filatov Meets U.S. Senators Nunn, Lugar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501203694 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1700 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0501203694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by V. Skvortsov; from the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Sergey Filatov, head of the presidential 
administration today met U.S. senators. 
  Democratic Senator Sam Nunn and republican Senator Richard 
Lugar represent those of America's political forces that support 
President Clinton's course toward large-scale economic 
cooperation with Russia. It is they who drew up the law on 
financial and technical assistance to Russia and the CIS 
countries in carrying through conversion and elimination of 
nuclear weapons. 
  Today the conversation was about the new Russian Parliament 
and how its work and interaction with the president will be 
organized. 
  Filatov said that the line-up of forces has already been 
determined. Now work with the factions is underway and 
questions of personnel and the agenda are being determined. The 
election results and the progress of reforms in Russia, plus 
questions of security, disarmament, and development of 
cooperation, will also be at the center of attention at the 
forthcoming meeting of the presidents of the two countries in 
Moscow next week. 

</TEXT>

