<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Orders Support for Russia-U.S. Enterprise Fund </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0501163394 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 5 Jan 94 
First Edition p 5 </F>

<F P=103> PM0501163394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Directive of the Russian Federation President on Measures </F>
To Assist the Activity of the Russia-U.S. Enterprise Fund," 
signed by President B. Yeltsin, and dated 27 December 1993, No. 
783-rp] 
  [Text] In connection with the creation of the Russia-U.S. 
Enterprise Fund (hereafter -- the Fund), whose aim is to assist 
the development of private business in Russia: 
  1. The Russian Federation Council of Ministers-Government is 
to offer the Fund every help in its activity. 
  2. The Russian State Committee for the Management of State 
Property is charged with coordinating work to assist the Fund's 
activity, liaising with the Russian Ministry of Finance and the 
Russian State Committee for Antimonopoly Policy and Support of 
the New Economic Structures. 
  3. The Russian State Committee for the Management of State 
Property is to resolve the question of granting the Fund 
premises on lease terms in the city of Moscow and in one city in 
the Far East region (to be suggested by the Fund) as official 
premises. 
  [Signed] Russian Federation President B. Yeltsin 
  [Dated] 27 December 1993, No. 783-rp 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

