<H3> <TI>   Relief Aid To Be Given to Former Yugoslavia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501214894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1616 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0501214894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Diplomatic Panorama" feature by diplomatic </F>
correspondents Dmitriy Voskoboynikov, Igor Porshnev, Vitaliy 
Trubetskoy and others] 
  [Text] Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin has 
signed a decision which says that Russia will provide relief aid 
estimated at 100 Mn rubles for former Yugoslavia. Hard currency 
expenditures associated with the relief aid baby food and 
medicines are not specified. 
  The aid will be handed over to Yugoslavia (Serbia and 
Montenegro), as well as to Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  This will be done to maintain the prestige of the Russian 
Federation and the international community's efforts in 
providing aid to the population of the former Yugoslavia 

</TEXT>

