<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Meets CIS Executive Secretary </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501165394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1210 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0501165394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 5 TASS -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin today met CIS Executive Secretary Ivan Korotchenya, who 
stopped over in Moscow en route to China. 
  According to information received from the Presidential 
Press 
Service, the sides have discussed prospects for implementing the 
agreements and documents signed during the CIS summit in 
Ashgabat. 
  President Yeltsin expressed satisfaction with the creative 
tendencies appearing within the Commonwealth, with the growing 
understanding of the need and inevitability of integrational 
processes. 
  As chairman of the CIS Heads of State Council, Yeltsin 
stressed the importance of stepping up the formation of a 
full-blooded and effective economic union and of strengthening 
collective security. 
  The sides also discussed some organisational measures, 
intended to consolidate the Commonwealth of Independent States, 
to enhance its authority on the international arena. 

</TEXT>

