<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Meets Kebich, Chernomyrdin 5 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501162294 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1532 
GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0501162294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 5 Jan (ITAR-TASS) -- President of the 
Russian Federation Boris Yeltsin today met Vyacheslav Kebich -- 
chairman of the Council of Ministers of the Republic of Belarus 
-- and chairman of the Government of the Russian Federation, 
Viktor Chernomyrdin. The meeting took place in the House of the 
Government of the Russian Federation. This was reported by the 
press service of the Goverment of the Russian Federation. 
  Questions of the forthcoming merger of the monetary system 
of 
the Republic of Belarus with the monetary system of the Russian 
Federation and of trade-and-economic cooperation were examined 
during the talks. 
  An accord was reached on the signing in the course of 
January 
of this year in the city of Minsk of a package of documents 
regulating this process. Other key issues of bilateral 
relations were also discussed. 

</TEXT>

