<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Belarus Leader Comments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501214594 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 2000 GMT 
5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0501214594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Russia must become a member of NATO before East 
European countries and Lithuania do so. Journalists were told 
this by Belarusian Prime Minister Vyacheslav Kebich after his 
talks with Viktor Chernomyrdin, head of the Russian government. 
The Belarusian prime minister believes that this step will make 
it possible to avoid military-political polarization in Europe. 
In this connection, Vyacheslav Kebich thinks that after 
Russia's admission to NATO Belarus may also become a member of 
the bloc. He stated that the question of the position of the 
two countries in respect of joining NATO will be discussed 
during the visit to Moscow next week by Stanislav Shushkevich, 
chairman of the Belarusian Supreme Soviet. This was reported by 
INTERFAX. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

