<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Border Troops Commander Satisfied With Azerbaijan Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501211194 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 1500 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0501211194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] In the first days of the new year, Andrey Nikolayev, 
commander of the Russian Federation's border troops, met 
President of Azerbaijan Geydar Aliyev in Baku and visited the 
Council of Ministers of the Republic of Dagestan. The trip is 
linked to the very difficult issues of guarding CIS state 
borders and of the security of internal borders and those with 
non-CIS states. 
  [Begin recording] [Andrey Nikolayev interviewed aboard 
plane, 
in flight] For two years there have been no serious, substantial 
contacts with Azerbaijan, with our colleagues in Azerbaijan, on 
the border issue. Much has been lost, but luckily not 
everything and an important result of the meeting in Azerbaijan 
was the fact that our colleagues in Azerbaijan and the president 
of Azerbaijan showed thorough understanding of the problems 
outlined by the Russian side -- Azerbaijan's entry into the CIS 
and joining the collective security treaty. Russia's goodwill 
and wish to provide for the national interests of Azerbaijan and 
Russia, and to protect the interests of other CIS states where 
Azerbaijan and Russia are concerned, create the conditions for 
settling the questions we are faced with. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

