<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Landsbergis Comments on NATO Membership Request </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0601111594 Vilnius ELTA NEWS BULLETIN in English 1844 GMT 
5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS0601111594 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius ELTA NEWS BULLETIN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From ELTA "NEWS BULLETIN" No. 408] </F>
  [Text] Vilnius, Jan 5 -- The right-wing opposition leader 
Vytautas Landsbergis made a statement concerning the official 
request for the membership in NATO: 
  "I hope that the West will notice the letter and request by 
Lithuanian president and Lithuania will stand next to Poland not 
only in the map, but in the list of candidates for NATO as well. 
Nobody can protest against that. We are striving for stability 
and security and this causes neither danger nor humiliation for 
anybody. 
  I also see that Lithuania's wish to become a member of NATO 
and its request do not contradict the agreement on Partnership 
For Peace. But the agreement on partnership will not serve as a 
substitute for conditions which should be fulfilled by Lithuania 
in order to become a member of NATO. This complies with the 
agreement on European security initiated by France and 
maintained by European Union. 
  It is very important that the process of peace and European 
consolidation in the Baltic region should not be disturbed by 
any non-democratic imperialistic forces". 

</TEXT>

