<H3> <TI>   Plans for Government Reshuffle Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MK0501143094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 5 Jan 94 
p 3 </F>

<F P=103> MK0501143094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed NEGA report in the "Estonia" column] </F>
  [Text] According to a report in the local press, four 
ministers are going to be replaced in the Estonian Government. 
Foreign Minister Trivimi Velliste is to be replaced by the 
current defense minister, Juri Luik. Trivimi Velliste himself 
will be sent to the United Nations as Estonia's permanent 
representative. The post of defense minister is to be ceded to 
parliament member Indrek Kannik. Finance Minister Madis Uurike 
is to be replaced by Kheyki Kranikh, a member of the liberal 
faction in the State Assembly, while Economics Minister Toomas 
Sildmae will give way to Toyvo Yurgenson, a deputy of the State 
Assembly. T. Sildmae's dismissal, however, has been opposed by 
representatives of Estonian entrepreneurial circles. Coming 
together for a hasty meeting on 3 January, they sent a joint 
letter of protest to the republic's president and prime 
minister. All the supposed candidates for ministerial posts are 
members of the ruling coalition in the State Assembly. A final 
decision is expected to be made before the first parliament 
session this year, scheduled for 10 January. 

</TEXT>

