<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Service Will Answer to President </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601093594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0809 
GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0601093594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 6 Jan -- The president of the Russian 
Federation has signed an edict endorsing the Statute on the 
Federal Counterintelligence Service (FCS) [Federalnaya Sluzhba 
Kontrrazvedki], which defines the tasks and structure of the 
service. The FCS public relations center announced this today. 
  The functions of the counterintelligence and antiterrorist 
units are defined and the powers of the FCS have been kept as 
far apart as possible from those of the law enforcement bodies. 
An FCS which performs functions outside their specialized 
service is ruled out. The total staff of the FCS will be 46 
percent less than that of the former Ministry of Security. 
  The statute envisions that the FCS will be directly 
subordinate to the president of the Russian Federation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

