<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Reportedly Returns Draft on Cabinet Reform </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501173594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1348 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0501173594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to well-informed sources, President Boris 
Yeltsin has returned to the government for reworking the draft 
decree on a cabinet reform. The draft was submitted to the 
president at the end of last year. Yeltsin discussed its 
details with Prime Minister Chernomyrdin and several other 
leading figures. 
  The sources say the president had questioned several key 
provisions of the draft. 
  The sources believe the resignation of Vice-Premiers 
Aleksandr Shokhin and Sergey Shakhray is a decided issue. They 
also feel Vice-Premiers Yuriy Yarov and Aleksandr Zaveryukha are 
going to be dropped from the cabinet too. As for Anatoliy 
Chubays, it is not clear whether he is going to leave the 
government altogether or remain the head of the State Property 
Committee without being a vice-premier. 

</TEXT>

