Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Information that an explosive device has been 
planted in the White House, where the Russian Government is to 
have its premises and where Prime Minister Chernomyrdin and some 
of his deputies have already moved in, and that an explosion 
there was imminent turned out to be false, INTERFAX has learned 
from (Litvinov), duty officer at Moscow's Main Internal Affairs 
Directorate. 
  At the same time, he said, operational measures to find the 
person who made the anonymous telephone call concerning the 
imminent explosion are continuing. Such anonymous calls can be 
regarded as malicious hooliganism and can entail imprisonment 
between one and five years in accordance with the criminal code. 
The spokesman said that the caller, who telephoned at around 
1730 on Tuesday, was a woman. 

