<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chernomyrdin Appeals to Independent Deputies in Duma </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501192894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1258 
GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0501192894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Pavel Kuznetsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 5 Jan -- This meeting with you -- who are of 
the land, of the people -- is very important to me, Russian 
Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin said today at a meeting with 
members of the Inter-Regional Association of Independent 
Deputies of the Federal Assembly's lower house. The government 
needs to know what stand independent deputies will take in the 
State Duma, he added. 
  Chernomyrdin stressed that the government would support any 
faction willing to work for the good of the country and called 
on deputies to establish firm cooperation between government and 
parliament based on a centrist position. He, in his turn, 
guaranteed to support constructive dialogue between the two 
branches of power. If necessary, I will come and meet you and 
bring the whole government with me, he said. 
  Chernomyrdin said the government would not be pursuing 
"popular" economic policies and that everything should be done 
to avoid a situation where the executive proposes "unpopular" 
and the legislative "popular" measures. 

</TEXT>

