<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shakhray Speaks on Future of State Duma </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501164994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1610 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0501164994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Pavel Kuznetsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, January 5 (TASS) -- "Deputies of the State 
Duma chairman should be elected on a parity basis: one from the 
election blocs and the other from individual constituencies," 
Russian Vice-Prime Minister Sergey Shakhray said. 
  Speaking at a meeting with the deputies of the State Duma 
from autonomous entities in Moscow on Wednesday, Shakhray said 
that "there have been attempts by large election blocs to 
predetermine the fate of the State Duma behind the back of the 
majority of deputies." He stressed that the Party of Russian 
Unity and Accord is ready for forming a broad coalition in the 
Duma "at least on the basis of a common approach towards the 
principle of election of the duma chairman." This would ensure 
the equality of all deputies. Additionally, all Duma leaders 
should be elected individually by secret ballot, Shakhray said. 
  He pointed out that a faction in the State Duma can include 
not less than 14 people which equals the number of seats each 
bloc has in the house if it has cleared the five per cent 
threshold. Shakhray added that a "faction begins to exist only 
after it has been registered by the Duma secretariat." 

</TEXT>

