<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Earmarks $500 Million for Parliament Complex </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0501165694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1131 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0501165694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Russian government has earmarked $500 Mn for 
the construction of a new parliament complex in Moscow. This 
was reported on Wednesday [5 January] to the organizing 
commission of the new parliament by Pavel Borodin, a 
presidential spokesman. He said that by the end of January 
contracts are going to be signed with a number of foreign 
construction companies. 
  According to Borodin, construction will begin on February 1 
and end by January 1 next year. He said there was every 
guarantee that the project would be completed in 10 months. 
  The complex will consist of an administrative building with 
a 
floorspace of 360,000 square meters and a 700-room hotel. It 
will be built in place of a stadium between Krasnopresnenskaya 
metro- station and the former building of parliament. 

</TEXT>

