<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gaydar Opposes Construction of Building </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601100894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0922 GMT 6 Jan 93 </F>
<F P=103> LD0601100894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Oleg Velichko] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 6 TASS -- Russian First Deputy Prime 
Minister Yegor Gaydar is against the idea to construct a new 
building for the Russian parliament and said the issue of 
appropriating 500 million US dollars for the purpose was not 
discussed by the government. 
  "If the discussion takes place I shall personally oppose 
it", 
he told TASS on Thursday. 
  Gaydar, who is the leader of the Russia's Choice 
parliamentary group, recalled that his bloc had already proposed 
to the Russian president to keep the existing parliament 
building, known as the "White House", for the new legislature. 
  "The position of the bloc on the given issue did not 
change", 
Gaydar said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

