<H3> <TI>   Moscow Editors To Strike </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601111194 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1000 GMT 
6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0601111194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The chief editors of virtually all newspapers 
published in Moscow have decided to strike on 10 January. They 
have taken this action because publishing houses have increased 
by several times the cost of their services, referring to a 
government decision on reassessing production assets. According 
to the editors, this will make the future existence of their 
publications impossible. KOMERSANT, which is not worried about 
any price rises, KRASNAYA ZVEZDA, which is restrained by army 
discipline, the NEW DAILY NEWSPAPER, which does not cooperate 
with the government and wants nothing from it, and the 
ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA, which believes that it is not the government 
but the printing trades who have incorrectly fixed tariffs that 
one should be fighting, will not be taking part in the strike. 

</TEXT>

