<H3> <TI>   Electoral Commission Announces New Polls in Tatarstan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601110294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1021 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0601110294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Ivan Novikov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 6 TASS -- The Russian Central 
Electoral Commission announced on Thursday that new elections to 
the Russian parliament will be held on March 13, 1994 in the 
Republic of Tatarstan where less than 50 per cent of the 
electorate came to the polls on December 12. 
  In the self-styled republic of Chechnya, where elections 
were 
not held at all, the new polls are also scheduled for March 13. 
  In other Russian constituencies where December elections 
failed new polls will be held either on March 6 or 26. 

