<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Resolution on Counterespionage Services Comes Into Effect </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0601180794 Kiev KIEVSKIYE VEDOMOSTI in Russian 4 Jan 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> WS0601180794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev KIEVSKIYE VEDOMOSTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Gennadiy Klyuchikov: "Fight Against Spies Remains </F>
a Current Issue in a Democracy as Well"] 
  [Text] The resolution "On Military Counterespionage 
Service of the Security Service of Ukraine" has come into 
effect, by virtue of Defense Minister Vitaliy Radetskyy's order. 
The Security Service has been entrusted with the 
counterespionage protection of the Armed Forces and other 
military units. The document specifies that the military 
counterespionage services shall effectively address defense 
problems, disclose and prevent espionage and sabotage activities 
in military units, as well as work out and implement measures to 
protect state secrets. 
  This way, the well-known special units, which were first 
introduced in the Russian Army on the eve of World War I, have 
outlived the Soviet Army, and have been transplanted into the 
reinstated military units of Ukraine. No matter where you go -- 
the fight against spies is always a current issue of any 
authorities. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-55226 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov005_f_94003" </HT>


