<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Looks Forward To Clinton Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601171794 Minsk Belarusian Foreign Ministry Department of 
Information in Russian 1513 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0601171794 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Belarusian Foreign Ministry Department of 
Information </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] S. Shushkevich has described the upcoming 
official visit by U.S. President Bill Clinton as an important 
and positive event for Belarus. As S. Shushkevich said in an 
interview with the ZVYAZDA newspaper correspondent, one of the 
most important tasks at the Belarus-U.S. talks is to clarify 
positions on the basic strategic issues of our policy and, in 
particular, issues concerning the security of Belarus. "When 
Belarus implements its constitutional law on neutrality and 
nuclear-free status it would like to have guarantees for the 
preservation of its neutral status, such as those that at one 
time Finland had from the United States and the USSR," stressed 
S. Shushkevich. 
  Concerning B. Clinton's "Partnership for Peace" initiative, 
S. Shushkevich noted that he also considers it expedient to 
examine the official strategy of Belarus in creating in Central 
Europe a belt of neutral states with certain guarantees from the 
great states of the world. 
  Furthermore, S. Shushkevich considers that B. Clinton's 
visit 
to Minsk will encourage U.S. investment in its economy. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

