<H3> <TI>   Kebich Says Russia Should Join NATO Before East Europe </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601174094 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1430 GMT 
6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0601174094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Russia should become a member of NATO before the 
states of Eastern Europe and Lithuania join this organization. 
This was stated by Belarusian Prime Minister Vyacheslav Kebich 
in an interview for a RIA correspondent. He said that such a 
step will help to avoid military-political polarization in 
Europe. Kebich believes that, once Russia has joined NATO, 
Belarus may also become a member of that bloc. 

</TEXT>

