<H3> <TI>   Kebich Praises Russian Government for Gas Deliveries </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0601155394 Minsk ZVYAZDA in Belarusian 31 Dec 93 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> WS0601155394 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk ZVYAZDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report] </F>
  [Text] Prime Minister Vyacheslav Kebich has received 
managers of the Russian joint stock company Gazprom. The 
meeting was dedicated to the issues connected with gas 
deliveries from the Russian Federation to our Republic until the 
year of 2010. An appropriate agreement was signed, in 
accordance with which Belarus will receive 16 billion cubic 
meters of gas as early as next year. In the future, the amount 
will double. Prime Minister Kebich praised the Russian 
Government for help in resolving the problems of winter gas 
deliveries to our Republic. The Belarusian side's request to 
reduce gas prices was received with understanding. 

</TEXT>

