<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Counting on EC Lifting Duty </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0601205894 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1815 
GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS0601205894 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belarusian Foreign Minister Petr Kravchanka has 
held talks with Magdalene Phoff, head of a Europarliament 
delegation for cooperation with CIS states. In the course of 
their conversation, the officials highlighted issues pertaining 
to the widening of Belarusian cooperation with the 
Europarliament and the European Council. Magdalene Phoff spoke 
in favor of expanding dialogue between the Europarliament and 
Belarus, and continuing negotiations on forming a reliable legal 
footing for mutually advantageous cooperation. The officials 
also discussed the problem of conventional arms reduction and 
nuclear disarmament. 
  Speaking of economic relations between Belarus and the EC, 
Petr Kravchanka underlined that the Republic is counting on the 
EC lifting its antidumping duties imposed on certain Belarusian 
products. 

</TEXT>

