<F P=102>  AU0601192494 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1800 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0601192494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Today at about 1000 [0800 GMT] vicar Teofan 
Sinaitul and the priest Sofian, head of the Antim monastery in 
Bucharest, arrived in Tiraspol intending to visit those who are 
imprisoned here: Ilie Ilascu, Tudor Petrov Popa, Andrei Ivantoc, 
Petru Godiac, and Alexandru Lesco. The two church officials 
were sent by Teoctist, patriarch of the Romanian Orthodox 
Church, to deliver a pastoral letter through which the patriarch 
comforts and blesses the prisoners, as well as a medal on behalf 
of the Holy Synod. 
  According to a statement by Teofan Sinaitul broadcast by 
Radio Chisinau, after they had persisted for almost eight hours, 
the authorities of the self-styled Dniester Republic did not 
authorize their meeting. We hope that in a few days' or weeks' 
time, when the authorities see fit to allow it, we will be able 
to pray for a few moments together with the five prisoners, 
Teofan said among other things, according to our Chisinau 
correspondent, Mircea Dascaliuc. 

</TEXT>

