<H3> <TI>   Turkey Ready on Projects </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601162994 Almaty KAZTAG in Russian 1330 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0601162994 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty KAZTAG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Prime Minister of Kazakhstan Sergey Tereshchenko 
received Turkish Transport Minister Makhmet Kostepen yesterday. 
[passage omitted] 
  Makhmet Kostepen said Turkey is ready to begin to implement 
several of specific proposals. For instance, Turkey is ready to 
participate in the reconstruction of Kazakhstani airports and to 
install electronic equipment there. 
  Cooperation in the field of telecommunications is also very 
promising. In February, Turkey, together with France, will 
launch a satellite which will substantially broaden the volume 
of Turkey's telecommunications with America, Western Europe, 
Central Asia, and Kazakhstan. 
  The guest also expressed a wish that an additional air 
flight 
to Turkey be opened. 
  Sergey Tereshchenko, having expressed hope that cooperation 
between the two countries will facilitate the speedy development 
of joint marine transportation, put forward the idea of setting 
up a joint venture for carrying freight by sea because each year 
about 7-10 million metric tons of oil have to be transported 
south and west. 

</TEXT>

