Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kazakhstan relies on sweeping aid by international 
financial agencies to be able to carry out its program of 
economic reforms, Premier Sergey Tereschenko told Western 
ambassadors in Almaty on Tuesday. 
  He hopes that European governments will help speed up 
financial aid to Kazakhstan which carries out economic reforms 
and a policy of tight crediting and finances relying on the 
IMF's assistance in luring western investment there. 
  The Prime Minister put the number of joint ventures 
