<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Discusses Use of 1994 Funds </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601144994 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Russian 0900 GMT 
6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0601144994 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Sergey Tereshchenko has met with the 
coordinating council of the fund for transforming the economy. 
The meeting discusses the Economics Ministry's proposals for 
using this year's money. The fund's goal is to support with 
investments reforms aimed at creating a socially oriented market 
economy and raising its competitiveness. 
  The meeting decided to channel the abovementioned funds into 
constructing and commissioning priority spheres of the economy, 
such as the power industry, the oil extraction and gas industry, 
nonferrous metallurgy, and the production of consumer goods. 
The meeting also decided to conserve a number of construction 
sites which cannot bring an immediate profit. 
  When finalizing the Cabinet of Ministry's draft statute, the 
Economics Ministry, along with other ministries and departments, 
should take into consideration foreign investments which will be 
attracted with this purpose in mind. 

</TEXT>

