<F P=103> LD0501225794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bishkek Kyrgyz Radio First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Kyrgyz </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Askar Akayev has received a letter from 
citizens of Toktogul district. It says that the people of 
Toktogul district, having familiarized themselves with the 
presidential program for social and economic development of 
Kyrgyzstan, fully support this important document aimed at 
lifting the country's economy out of crisis. Citizens of the 
district assure the president that they will do everything to 
implement it successfully. The letter also spoke about a 
forthcoming referendum. On 30 January citizens of the region 
intend to confirm at the referendum that the president, who was 
elected by the nation on 12 December 1991 for a period of five 
years, is the president of Kyrgyzstan until the end of his term 
with all the powers ascribed to the post. The letter has been 
signed by 16 people on behalf of labor veterans and workers of 
Toktogul district. 

