<F P=102>  LD0501181694 Bishkek Kyrgyz Radio First Program Network in 
Kyrgyz 0000 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0501181694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bishkek Kyrgyz Radio First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Kyrgyz </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Rustembekov, the state secretary of [word 
indistinct] of the Kyrgyz Republic held an expanded sitting with 
the participation of leaders of the State Committee for National 
Security, the Interior Ministry, the procurator's office, and a 
number of ministries, departments, and banks. The participants 
familiarized themselves with the president's latest 
instructions, which he had signed on the eve of the meeting. 
These documents concern strict observance of the government's 
resolution on the urgency of specifically targeted social 
protection of the population. Urgent measures were discussed in 
order to swiftly tackle the emerging problems. 
  The head of state set up working commissions that will 
control the accuracy and timeliness of paying wages, pensions, 
and stipends. These commissions, which consist of the 
president's apparatus' personnel, will be visiting all regions 
of the republic in accordance with a relevant schedule. They 
must submit the results of their audit by 15 January. The state 
secretary under the president will coordinate this work. 
  The working groups are led by: Bakayev, chairman of the 
State Security Committee; Interior Minister Sutalinov; 
Procurator General Sharshenaliyev; Justice Minister 
Cholponbayev; Finance Minister Shakirov; Khakimov, minister of 
labor and social protection; and Kunakov, director of the State 
Taxation Inspectorate. 
  Senior officials of the government's apparatus will 
cooperate 
with them. Members of the working commission have left for the 
regions. 

</TEXT>

