<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Renewed Azerbaijani Offensive Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0601154594 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1400 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0601154594 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1400 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The situation remains exceedingly tense on Karabakh 
fronts. The Nagorno-Karabakh Republic [NKR] Defense Army press 
service reported that after a brief lull in fighting at night, 
the Azerbaijani troops resumed their attacks today in the 
direction of Gadrut, Agdam, and Askeran under the cover of 
fierce artillery shelling of Karabakh's defensive positions. 
Having massed large forces on the front, the enemy is trying at 
all costs to breach Karabakh's positions in these sectors. 
  NKR Defense Army subunits are succeeding in halting the 
numerically superior Azerbaijani troops. Nevertheless, the 
Azerbaijanis moved forward in the southern sector on the evening 
of 5 January. 
  The battles are also continuing with alternating success in 
the north, near Matagis in Mardakertskiy Rayon, where in recent 
days the Karabakh forces have managed to push back the enemy to 
its initial positions. 
  The battles were still continuing on all the aforementioned 
sectors at 1100 today. Both sides are suffering losses. 
  Information gathered from radio interception indicate that 
during the attacks the Azerbaijanis used assault detachments of 
foreign mercenaries, most of them from the CIS countries. 

</TEXT>

