<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parliament Debating Bill on Martial Law </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0601200594 Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network in Azeri 1600 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0601200594 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Azeri </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The National Assembly is holding its regular session 
today. Our correspondent Gulsafa Ahmedova reports: 
  [Ahmedova] Deputy Chairman of the Supreme Soviet Afiaddin 
Dzhalilov chaired the National Assembly session. 
  Though the bill on martial law was endorsed [as the basis 
for 
further debate] at its first reading at one of the previous 
session of the National Assembly, in view of proposals that have 
been made, it was recommitted to the relevant commission for 
amendments. 
  Metleb Mutallimov, chairman of the commission, submitted the 
new version of the bill to the parliamentarians. A new debate 
began. Its importance for the republic that is living under war 
conditions was noted. 
  Tofik Gasymov, chairman of the commission that drafted the 
bill on border guards, briefed the National Assembly about the 
bill. The parliamentarians put forward a number of interesting 
proposals during the debate. The bill was then put to a vote 
paragraph by paragraph. It was adopted on the condition that 
some editorial changes be made to it. 
  The parliamentarians then expressed their agreement with the 
removal of the Deputy Prime Minister Vakhid Akhmedov and Finance 
Minister Salekh Mamedov from their posts. 
  The bill on the legislative plan for the first quarter of 
1994 was debated and adopted in full after certain proposals 
were taken into account. 
  The National Assembly was continuing its session when our 
newscast went on the air. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

