<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Discuss Deployment Problems </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0601201794 Baku TURAN in English 1656 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0601201794 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baku, JANUARY 6 (TURAN) -- Today President Geydar 
Aliyev of Azerbaijan received the commander of the 
Transcaucasian group of Russian troops General-Colonel Fedor 
Reut on his request. The meeting took place behind closed doors. 
  One of the representatives of the Presidential team told 
TURAN agency that during the talks President Aliyev touched upon 
the problem of participation by Russian troops stationed in 
Armenia fighting on Armenia's side. The general said that the 
Russian Army is not interfering in the conflict. In addition, 
he said that he will strictly control the troops who serve under 
him. General Reut thanked the President for his assistance to 
the Russian party for the transportation of military goods 
through the territory of Azerbaijan. Other problems of the 
region were also discussed during the talks. 

</TEXT>

