<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iranian Officials Discuss Border, Trade Affairs </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0601204894 Baku TURAN in English 1656 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0601204894 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baku, January 6 (TURAN) -- Yesterday the 
vice-chairman of the Supreme Soviet of Azerbaijan, Afiaddin 
Dzhalilov, received a delegation from the Ardebil province of 
Iran headed by the Vice- Governor 'Ali Akbar Iskanderi. The 
sides discussed ways of broadening and maintaining relations 
between the bordering regions of the two countries. 
  Dzhalilov expressed his satisfaction with the Iranian 
party's 
assistance to Azerbaijani refugees and displaced persons and the 
citizens of Nakhichevan which is under blockade. 
  Vice-Premier Abbas Abbasov also received the Iranian 
Ambassador to Azerbaijan, 'Ali Asgar Nahavandian, yesterday as 
well as other members of the delegation which include Mayor 'Ali 
Akbarzade of the town of Belasuvar, bisected by the 
Iranian-Azerbaijani border, and the Secretary of Trade, Ahmad 
Kazemi. 
  During these talks, both sides discussed the broadening of 
border relations. Of particular focus was the creation of a 
free trade zone in the Iranian-Azerbaijani town of Belasuvar. 
As known, at the end of last year the Cabinet of Ministers of 
Azerbaijan passed a decree on the creation of the free trade 
zone in this sector of the border. However, the opening of the 
zone has been delayed for technical causes. 

</TEXT>

