<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Border Bazaars Planned </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601201694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1427 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0601201694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Azerbaijan's Vice-Premier Abbas Abbasov and a 
delegation from the Iranian province of Ardebil discussed in 
Baku on Wednesday [5 January] ways of opening bazaars along the 
common border. 
  Abbasov reported that his government had drafted a plan on 
joint bazaars, and the republican leadership had been doing all 
it could to open such markets. 
  The project provides for stimulating the delivery of food 
and 
other prime necessity items to Azerbaijan from Iran. There will 
be primarily barter trade to keep Azerbaijan's currency reserves 
intact. Proceeds from market sales will be exempted from taxes. 
  Abbasov spoke highly of Iran's humanitarian relief to 
Azerbaijani refugees and welcomed Iran's proposal to set up a 
chain of Iranian shops in Azerbaijan. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

