<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Repeat Elections' To Be Held in Some Regions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601232894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1726 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0601232894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Central Election Commission has announced the 
date of elections to the Federal Assembly in Russia's regions 
where they were not held or were boycotted. 
  A representative of the Commission told INTERFAX that on 
March 13 elections would be held in Tatarstan (the Volga 
region). On the same day elections to the State Duma will be 
held in some of this republic's one-mandate electoral districts, 
including the Naberezhniye Chelny, Almetyevsk, Nizhnekamsk, and 
Privolzhsk districts. 
  Pending repeat elections, candidates will be advanced and an 
election campaign will be held. 
  On March 26, elections to the Federation Council will take 
place in the Chelyabinsk two-mandate electoral district, and on 
March 6 in the Yamalo-Nenets electoral district. 
  The Central Election Commission reports that the elections 
will be organized by the local election commissions consisting 
of the same members and held in the same polling stations on the 
basis of the adjusted lists of electors. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

