<H3> <TI>   Experts Suggest Localities Adjust Constitutions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601234494 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1700 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0601234494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Experts from the Council of Heads of Administrations 
attached to the Russian president have suggested to Boris 
Yeltsin that he should set up commissions to bring the 
constitutions of the republics within Russia in line with the 
constitution of the Russian Federation. 
  Analysis carried out recently has revealed that the 
constitutions adopted in Tatarstan, Bashkortastan, and Tyva not 
long ago contradict the Russian Constitution in a number of 
norms. 

</TEXT>

