<H3> <TI>   Groznyy Accuses Russia of Reluctance To Quit Gendarme Role </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601172494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1427 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0601172494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Chechen Republic has described the proposal by 
the Central Election Commission that it take part in the 
parliamentary elections on March 13 as an ultimatum which will 
aggravate confrontation. 
  INTERFAX correspondents report that the official Groznyy 
accused Russia of unwillingness to quit the gendarme approach, 
as well as the policy of threats and intimidation. 
  The Chechen Republic believes that the date of March 13 is 
nothing else than a new deadline for the existence of the 
Chechen Republic to be possibly followed by punishment of the 
"obstinate". 

</TEXT>

