<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Orenburg Region To Create Government </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601162494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1345 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0601162494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In line with the recent decision by the head of the 
local administration Vladimir Yelagin, the Orenburg Region will 
have its own government. The resolution on the issue says that 
the Cabinet is to be formed proceeding from provisions of 
Yeltsin's decrees of October 22 and December 22, 1993 on 
measures to improve the activities of local executive bodies of 
power. 
  The staff of the administration head, which will exist in 
parallel with the local government, is to be cut by 20 percent. 
  The similar two-level executive structure was first created 
in 1992 by the former governor of the Sverdlovsk Region Eduard 
Rossel, who was dismissed by Yeltsin's decree. Now Rossel is 
the president of the Association of Economic Interaction of the 
Ural Region. He is also elected deputy to the new Russian 
Parliament. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

