<H3> <TI>   Federation Council To Be Under Presidential Administration </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601163494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1427 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0601163494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Russian Vice-Premier Sergey Shakhray told an 
Interfax interviewer on Thursday that there is a plan to 
re-subordinate the State Committee for Federation Affairs and 
Nationalities he leads to the presidential administration. 
  Commenting on the project, he suggested that such a move 
would make the committee less effective. He said the committee 
could be more productive under the government's command. But 
within the presidential administration it would turn into a 
secondary department. He voiced conviction that the plan had 
been devised because of his personality and re-emphasized the 
need for leading the committee by a vice-premier, as usual. 
Otherwise, in his words, it is impossible to make the finance 
and other ministries and departments turn their attention to 
ethnic relations and regional problems. However, he added, 
"there is every indication that a different decision has been 
taken." 
  He believes that there must be a body to work out political 
recommendations for the president on ethnic and regional 
policies. As for the federation committee, it should implement 
presidential and government decisions in this sphere. 

</TEXT>

