<H3> <TI>   New Structure for Relations With Constitutent Members </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601223994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1726 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0601223994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sources in presidential circles reported to Interfax 
that a new structure to be in charge of ties with constituent 
members is supposed to be created in the government currently 
under reorganization. Vice Premier Yuriy Yarov is expected to 
head it. 
  The new structural body is to be created on the basis of the 
State committee on the Federation and nationalities and the 
unification of several other structures. 
  The sources indicated that the present State committee on 
the 
Federation would be withdrawn from the influence of the Party of 
Russian Unity and Concord [PRUC] headed by the vice premier and 
leader of the state committee Sergey Shakhray. 
  Ramazan Abdulatipov, another prominent functionary of the 
PRUC, works as deputy chairman of the State committee on the 
Federation. PRUC member Aleksandr Kotenkov heads one of the 
major structural branches of the committee. 

</TEXT>

