<H3> <TI>   Independents Form Parliamentary Group in State Duma </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601162294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1345 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0601162294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Forty five State Duma deputies elected in 
single-seat constituencies have set up a parliamentary group of 
independents and adopted a declaration and provisional rules. 
They will press for equality of party and other parliamentary 
groups. 
  The group will be headed by Gennadiy Kalistratov, former 
people's deputy. In the former Supreme Soviet of Russia he was 
deputy chairman of the Industry and Energy Committee and a 
member of the Industrial Union group. 
  Independent deputies had a meeting with Prime Minister 
Viktor 
Chernomyrdin in Moscow Wednesday. They called for a better 
social protection of the population in the government's reform 
program. 

</TEXT>

