<H3> <TI>   Military for Democracy Movement Favors State Control </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601134894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1316 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0601134894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Sergey Ostanin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 6 TASS -- The coordinating council of 
the Military for Democracy Movement has supported the idea to 
create a system of state political control over power 
structures. Its statement, received by ITAR-TASS today, pointed 
out that the absence of such control "resulted in the 
self-isolation of the armed forces and the work of the military 
leadership without taking into consideration the economic and 
political processes in Russia." As a result of it, authors of 
the statement believe, "social tension among servicemen 
heightened both in the Army and the Navy." 
  The Military for Democracy Movement urged the Russian 
president and government to "take all necessary measures for 
improving the situation in the power structures of the Russian 
Federation, for which the personnel policy should be shaped 
directly by the Russian president." 

</TEXT>

