<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Associate Accuses Shakhray of Splitting Activity </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601161494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1345 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0601161494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sergey Shakhray, the PRUC (Party of Russian Unity 
and Concord) leader, is engaged in a splitting activity which 
will increase the confrontational trends even before the State 
Duma opens, Interfax was told by a senior official in the 
presidential headquarters who preferred to remain anonymous. He 
noted that Shakhray called a meeting of Duma members who were 
elected in single-mandate districts from the republics 
incorporated in Russia. Following Shakhray's speech, 15 deputies 
of Tuva, Yakutia, Karachayevo-Cherkessia, Mari-El, Dagestan, 
Ingushetia, North Ossetia and other autonomies declared the 
setting up of a group which would nominate Sergey Shakhray for 
the position of the State Duma speaker. The deputies said that 
the group will work for implementation of the Federative Treaty. 
They want this group to be given the standing of a 
parliamentary party to be able to contribute to the formation of 
the State Duma bodies. 

</TEXT>

