<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Orders Adjusted Hold-Over Budget for First Quarter </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0501160994 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 5 Jan 94 
First Edition p 5 </F>

<F P=103> PM0501160994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Edict No. 2282 of the Russian Federation president "On </F>
Financing State Expenditure from the Russian Federation's 
Republic Budget in the First Quarter of 1994," dated Moscow, the 
Kremlin, 24 December 1993 and signed by Russian Federation 
President B. Yeltsin] 
  [Text] For the purposes of ensuring continuous financing 
of state expenditure from the Russian Federation's republic 
budget until the adoption of the Russian Federation Law "On the 
Republic Budget of the Russian Federation for 1994" and in 
accordance with Points 2 and 3 of the Russian Federation 
president's Edict No. 1598 of 7 October 1993 "On Legal 
Regulation During the Period of Stage-by-Stage Constitutional 
Reform in the Russian Federation," I decree that: 
  1. The Russian Federation Council of Ministers-Government is 
to be permitted to finance state programs and measures in the 
first quarter of 1994 proceeding from the Russian Federation 
republic budget's expenditure for the fourth quarter of 1993, 
established by the Russian Federation president's Edict No. 2234 
of 21 December 1993 "On Amplifying the Indicators of the Russian 
Federation Republic Budget for the Fourth Quarter of 1993" and 
with due regard for the 90-percent increase in the minimum 
compensation as of 1 December 1993 in accordance with the 
Russian Federation president's Edict No. 2115 of 5 December 1993. 
  2. In the first quarter of 1994 part of the revenues from 
excise duties and value-added tax is to be transferred to the 
budgets of the components of the Russian Federation according to 
the normatives laid down in Article 4 of the Russian Federation 
Law "On the Republic Budget of the Russian Federation for 1993." 
  3. The Central Bank of the Russian Federation is to grant 
credit to the Russian Federation Council of Ministers-Government 
in the first quarter of 1994 to finance the expenditure of the 
Russian Federation's republic budget in the sum of 7.5 trillion 
rubles [R], including R300 billion to finance defense industry 
conversion programs on a return basis and R400 billion to 
finance investment programs, for a 10-year period, with 
repayment in equal instalments starting in 1998, calculated on 
the basis of 10 percent per annum. 
  4. The Russian Federation Ministry of Finance is to: 
  ensure the financing of the expenditure of the Russian 
Federation's republic budget in the first quarter of 1994 as 
revenues enter the budget, with due regard for Central Bank of 
the Russian Federation credit; 
  transfer from the Russian Federation's republic budget to 
the 
budgets of the components of the Russian Federation in the first 
quarter of 1994 subsidies and subventions to equalize the level 
of social provision for the population in the volumes envisaged 
for these purposes in the fourth quarter of 1993 and corrected 
for the increase as of 1 December 1993 in the minimum 
compensation in accordance with the Russian Federation 
president's Edict No. 2115 of 5 December 1993 and for the size 
of the Russian Federation republic budget arrears formed during 
1993 in relation to this expenditure. 
  5. In order to change the terms for granting long-term 
credit allocated in accordance with Point 1 of the Russian 
Federation Supreme Soviet Decree No. 3125-1 of 26 June 1992 "On 
Granting Long-Term Credit to the Russian Federation Ministry of 
Finance" and Point 8 of the Russian Federation Supreme Soviet 
Decree No. 4130-1 of 18 December 1992 "On Bringing into Force 
the Russian Federation Law 'On Amplifying the Indicators of the 
Russian Federation Republic Budget for 1992,'" the Russian 
Federation Ministry of Finance is to be permitted to start 
paying interest as of January 1994 to the Central Bank of the 
Russian Federation calculated on the basis of 10 percent per 
annum. 
  6. The Russian Federation Ministry of Finance is to be 
entrusted, jointly with the Russian Federation Pension Fund and 
with due regard for the results of the implementation of the 
Pension Fund budget in 1993, with examining the question of 
extending to the first quarter of 1994 the validity of Article 7 
of the Russian Federation Law "On the Republic Budget of the 
Russian Federation for 1993." 
  7. This edict is to be submitted to the Russian Federation 
Federal Assembly for examination. 
  8. This edict comes into force the moment it is published. 
  [Signed] Russian Federation President B. Yeltsin 
  [Dated] 24 December 1993 

</TEXT>

