<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry Stops Financing Military Courts </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MK0601130094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 6 Jan 94 
p 2 </F>

<F P=103> MK0601130094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report in the "In Brief" column] </F>
  [Text] Moscow -- Under an order by Colonel General Vasiliy 
Vorobyev, chief of the Main Military Budget and Finance 
Directorate of the Russian Federation Defense Ministry, as of 1 
January 1994 the allocation of funds in Russian or foreign 
currency from the Russian Federation Defense Ministry budget for 
the payment of allowances, salaries, material values, and 
communal and other services to Russian Federation military 
courts will be terminated. This order was issued "in line with 
the 24 December 1993 letter by the Russian Federation Finance 
Ministry" and in execution of the Russian Federation Government 
decree on approving of the Statute on the Russian Federation 
Ministry of Justice. According to this statute, the Justice 
Ministry is tasked with ensuring the requisite conditions for 
the functioning of general jurisdiction and military courts. As 
has become known, however, this decision has come as a total 
surprise for the ministry's leadership because the statute says 
nothing about financing military courts. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

