<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Servicemen's Pay Raise Triggers Pension Revaluation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0601184194 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 5 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM0601184194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Petr Altunin report under the "Yesterday" rubric: </F>
"Military Pensions Being Recalculated"] 
  [Text] As has already been reported in KRASNAYA ZVEZDA of 
31 December 1993, basic pay and pay according to rank is being 
increased by a factor of 1.9 for servicemen in the Russian Armed 
Forces from 1 January 1994 in accordance with a Russian 
Federation Government decree. 
  The Ministry of Defense Main Directorate for the Military 
Budget and Finance announced: The Russian Federation Law On the 
Provision of Pensions to Servicemen (Article 49) and the decree 
of the Russian Federation Council of Ministers/Government of 22 
September 1993, No.941 (Article 14) says: If the monetary 
allowance for servicemen increases, pensions which have been 
previously fixed for discharged servicemen and members of their 
families are also subject to review from the same date. The 
military commissariats have already set about this work. 
  Many people are interested in the current minimum wage 
which, 
as we know, is taken into consideration when reviewing military 
pensions. It stands today at 14,620 rubles. 

</TEXT>

