<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage on Gamsakhurdia's Reported Death </TI></H3>
<H4>   Investigation Outside Zugdidi </H4>
<F P=102> LD0701114194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1128 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0701114194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tengiz Pachkoria] </F>
  [Text] Tbilisi January 7 TASS -- "So far we have not 
received any concrete facts confirming or denying reports of 
Gamsakhurdia's death and burial in one of the districts of 
western Georgia", Head of the Zugdidi District Administration 
Edisher Chargazia told ITAR- TASS on Friday. 
  Chargazia confirmed that an investigation is underway in the 
Zugdidi district and outlying areas. The investigation is being 
directed by the republic's Deputy Procurator-General Anzor 
Baluashvili. 
  Deputy Chairman of the Provisional Committee for Emergencies 
in Western Georgia Vakhtang Kvaratskhelia told ITAR-TASS that 
the investigative committee left Zugdidi today for the 
neighboring Tsalendzhikhi district, where it will visit two 
villages, Nakipu and Dzhagira. It was in this district that the 
rumor started of Gamsakhurdia's death and burial in one of the 
above-mentioned villages. 
  Kvaratskheliya himself proposes that "Zviad Gamsakhurdia's 
death did not occur in one of the districts of western Georgia, 
but beyond the republic's borders". 

</TEXT>

