<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage on Gamsakhurdia's Reported Death </TI></H3>
<H4>   Officials Sent to Chechnya </H4>
<F P=102> LD0701115194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1127 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0701115194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tengiz Pachkoriya] </F>
  [Text] Tbilisi January 7 TASS -- Late Thursday evening a 
group of Georgian law enforcement officials took a chartered 
plane out of Tbilisi to Groznyy, capital of the Chechen 
republic, Georgian First Deputy Minister of Security Avtandil 
Ioseliani told ITAR-TASS on Friday. The officials intend to 
meet with the person who first informed Manana Gamsakhurdia and 
the Chechen leadership about the death of Zviad Gamsakhurdia, 
the ousted president of Georgia. The goal of the trip is to 
determine the accuracy of the reports about Gamsakhurdia's death. 
  Ioseliani stressed that the group's fact-finding trip to 
Chechnya became possible due to an agreement reached with a 
delegation from Chechnya, visiting Tbilisi. The Georgian 
officials from the foreign ministry, security ministry, and 
procurator's office left for Groznyy together with the returning 
Chechen delegation. 

</TEXT>

