<H3> <TI>   Reportage on Gamsakhurdia's Reported Death </TI></H3>
<H4>   Investigation Continues </H4>
<F P=102> LD0701055794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0445 
GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0701055794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Aleksandr Chernov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 7 Jan -- Law enforcement officials sent by 
the Georgian head of state to the alleged site of Zviad 
Gamsakhurdia's death are continuing their work. 
  A duty officer of the Georgian Ministry of Security told 
ITAR-TASS over the phone that no news has come overnight. The 
former president's death is not being denied, but no version has 
been confirmed so far, and no information on the location of the 
body has been obtained. 
  The duty officer of the Georgian Security Ministry believes 
that information that can shed light on the death of Zviad 
Gamsakhurdia can be expected by late morning or early afternoon. 

</TEXT>

