<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Justice Ministry Discusses Referendum on Status </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601213994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1906 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0601213994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Abkhazia's Justice Ministry, temporarily based in 
Tbilisi, has evaluated the referendum on the legal status of 
this autonomous republic as a political farce. 
  The Justice Ministry's statement, distributed on Thursday, 
says that the aim of this measure is "to announce Abkhazia as a 
sovereign state" despite the UN and Security Council decisions. 
(As is known, their resolutions reconfirm Georgia's sovereignty 
and territorial integrity.) 
  "The intention to hold a referendum at a time when ethnic 
cleansing and genocide of the Georgian population are underway 
in Abkhazia is cynical," underlines the statement. 
  To this effect the ministry declared that "according to 
Georgia's laws and norms of international law, results of this 
referendum will have no legal force." 

</TEXT>

