<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Hopeful for Successful Summit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1101105794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1034 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1101105794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Talalayev] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 11 TASS -- Press secretary of the 
Russian President Vyacheslav Kostikov has expressed the hope 
that the Russo-American summit meeting, which is to begin here 
today, would contribute to the strengthening of bilateral 
cooperation. 
  Replying to reporters within the building of the Council of 
the Federation, which held its first meeting here, Kostikov 
noted that the sides would "negotiate comprehensively and 
seriously" the relations between Russia and the United States. 
He believes that the U.S. President will explain in greater 
detail the American "partnership for peace" initiative. "Russia 
has no reasons to keep aloof of this initiative," the press 
secretary stressed. "It only remains to see to what extent its 
implementation meets the national interests of Russia. 
  Kostikov described as sharp and prompt the Russian Foreign 
Ministry's reaction to the unlawful actions of the Lithuanian 
authorities against two Russian generals. He said that "at 
present this reaction is adequate". "But the reaction of the 
president and of Russia might be even tougher if such incidents 
were to reoccur in the future, even very tough compared to world 
precedents," the press secretary stated. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>
